From 033b1a70467ccd08c971fccec68587352acbf533 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 05:45:20 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 005/174] PGCL: fix COW clustering, SMP boot, i915 driver, and
 TTM buddy manager
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

COW clustering: fix sub-page comparison in wp_page_copy() to use
page_folio() instead of raw struct page* — sub-pages within the same
kernel page have different struct page pointers.  Reduces COW faults
from 257 to 21 for 256 sub-pages (~12x improvement).

SMP boot: fix AP triple-fault caused by NX bit on trampoline code.
With PAGE_MMUSHIFT>0, set_real_mode_permissions must still call
set_memory_x on trampoline text (accepts W+X trade-off for AP boot).

i915 driver: comprehensive MMUPAGE audit across scatterlist, vma,
gem, memory_region, TTM buddy manager, GVT, and display subsystems.
Convert DMA/GPU page operations from PAGE_SHIFT to MMUPAGE_SHIFT
where hardware page granularity matters.

Swap-in clustering: disabled with #if 0 — order-0 folios are not
compound pages under PGCL, so swap treats each sub-page independently.
Re-enabling requires swap subsystem PGCL-awareness.

Also: fix RSS accounting in finish_fault, suppress expected W+X
warnings at PAGE_MMUSHIFT>0, add /proc/meminfo PageSize/BasePageSize.

Tested: PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 (64KB/4KB) boots with SMP=4, all clustering
and fork tests pass.  PAGE_MMUSHIFT=0 regression test passes.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
